  "prompt": "Why do people give presents/gifts?",
  "response": "People give presents or gifts for various reasons:\n\n1. Social bonding\n- To show affection and care\n- To strengthen relationships\n- To express love or friendship\n\n2. Celebration\n- Birthdays\n- Weddings\n- Holidays\n- Graduations\n- Other special occasions\n\n3. Cultural and traditional reasons\n- Religious ceremonies\n- Cultural rituals\n- Reciprocating hospitality\n\n4. Emotional expression\n- Gratitude\n- Appreciation\n- Sympathy\n- Apology\n- Congratulations\n\n5. Social expectations\n- Following social norms\n- Maintaining social connections\n- Showing respect\n\n6. Personal motivations\n- Desire to make someone happy\n- Feeling of personal satisfaction\n- Building goodwill\n\n7. Practical purposes\n- Helping someone in need\n- Supporting a cause\n- Exchanging goods or services\n\n8. Marking milestones\n- Commemorating achievements\n- Recognizing significant life events\n- Celebrating personal or professional success\n\n9. Diplomatic or business reasons\n- Building professional relationships\n- Networking\n- Maintaining strategic connections\n\nGift-giving is a complex social behavior that serves multiple psychological, emotional, and practical functions across different cultures and contexts.",
